items.text: Terry Katong Laksa is creamy & tasty, but smaller than expected quantity of laksa for $3.50. Claims not to have MSG nor sugar
Grilled fish & fried oyster.
Love the hokkien mee!
Do not miss the carrot cake. The white version is one of the best rendition you can find in Singapore.
satay bee hoon, western food, fish porridge, chicken rice, carrot cake cannot miss. look carefully u will knw which stall to go.
HK Yummy Soup moved to West Coast Hawker Centre.
Vegetarian stall serves excellent thunder tea rice! Chockful of fresh veg toppings
成兴海南鸡饭. 51, Upper Bukit Timah Road, #02-177, Bukit Timah Market & Food Centre, Singapore 588215. Open: 11am - 3pm. Rest on Sun.
The carrot cake is a must-try
Yummy yummy carrot cake!!
#02-145's hokkien mee is one of the worst I've had, and it's going at $3.50 for the smallest serving. Very unimpressed.
#02-177 chicken rice yummy but long Q :(
Pizzaria creations. Passable lasagne.
The fish soup is gd.
Tip Top Beef Brisket ..shiok 
be there before evening to try out the fast-selling delicious tom yum soup.
The mutton soup is still here!! Must try!!
Must try the Steam Chicken Wing In Lotus Leaf at Hong Kong Yummy Soups stall #02-121
leng kee sliced fish bee hoon: one of the best of its kind. they are generous with the fish slices, the chilli has the oomph factor and the soup is flavorful. healthy food seldom tastes so good!
Chai tow kway (fried carrot cake) shootout betw Seng Kee #02-182 & He Zhong #02-185. Both r tasty. SK's fried pieces r firm & savoury. HZ's is fluffier & more fragrant, & their eggs more fried
The kway chap is a must try !!
Seng Kee carrot cake is the best !
Corner stall facing the link bridge selling soya bean is the freshest and cheapest (at 70cts per cup) you can find in the west.
The 144 fish soup is not as fantastic as it claimed. Peppery soup with fish slice. Not a trace of veggies in the soup.
One of the busier breakfast stalls on a working day. Sheng Cheng #02-165 prepares minced meat fishball noodles. Ask for lar pok (fried pork lard cubes) for an added oomph!
try stall 02-145 for the best Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee
Fish soup stall 14X looks so-so $1 more than the other stall behind near side staircase. But chilli paste is good. Soup has less fishy smell during or after taste even without much vegetables.
Don't buy the fried kway Teow from the something Kee stall.
The new dim sum stall -  banana red bean fritters not bad, but dun bother abt the Liu sha Bao, v oily! Char SIEW Bao so so... Sweet taste type
Variety of western, Indian and Muslim foods.
Seng Kee Carrot Cake is a must try!
yummy bak chor mee @ stall #02-165. Open daily till 12pm only though.
Try the fruit juice at fresh juice ice blend :3
Must try Ah Poh BBQ Seafood! Best stingray!
Super diluted sugar cane juice from stall #02-122. Avoid.
Kopi. According to an elderly local who lives in the neighbourhood (forever), the top kopi stalls are: Hainan (#02-163), Hup Cheong (#02-173) & Eng Kee (#02-169) — in that order
Try Peter Pan's Western Food for its delicious meats!
Very nice l love to eat
Porridge not bad. Tasty. Can try.
Peter pan western is da bomb. Try the pork or chicken cutlet.
Fishball noodles. Lee Kwang Kee #03-179 serves without 'her giao' (fish dumpling). Signature bowl comes with slices of large fish cakes (normal & spicy). Likewise for their factory-made fishballs
Kuay chap & 166 bak chu mee.. always loooooong queue..

the thunder tea rice at the vegetarian stall is so big n good.   the steamed egg at the steamed stall pits the steamed egg on top of a pork patty, not just a little minced pork. for 2.80.  good n deal
Chicken wings are nice..yum yum!
靓靓靓：汤水很鲜甜魚又新鲜。水粿很有古早味米味也很浓
Must try HONG WEN MUTTON SOUP, direct in from of the main stair.
The real Penang signature laksa! Nice #02-128
Hokkien mee!!
God bless the katong laksa at #02-194!
Satay bee hoon is a must have!
Chee Cheong Fun is super good! :) The one that the couple is selling. :D
Stall 133: Penang Authentic. Char Kuey Teow that's pretty close to home (Penang of course!!!)
Hokkien Mee. Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee #02-145 serves it wet and tasty. Generous ingredients. Slurp!
Must hv the kuey chap. Come early to queue and avoid after 10am else everything sold out!
Xie kee hokkian mee is da bezt!
Ya Bao noodle stall must try!
Love the mutton soup..had been eating it for almost 15yrs! 
Check out the girl working at Hainan coffee stall XD
Seng Kee Carrot Cake ftw!
Stall 02-189 with simple sign "Nasi Lemak Zha Kueh Min Jian Kueh" makes their mi chiam kueh (Chinese pancake) individually. Soft batter style. 2 filling options: peanuts or tau sar (red bean paste)
The wanton  with black sauce here is the best.
Lots of gd food though most closes by 9pm. Fish soup, satay beehoon, hokkien mee, wanton mee, black carrotcake
Penang char kway teow. A much welcome addition to our hawker fare. I go here when I'm looking for a change. 133 Penang Authentic #02-193 is run by true Penangites. Generous ingredients in CKT
BBQ Chicken wings, Satay bee hoon, n Hokkien mee muz try!! :)
Remember to try the fish porridge. Open since 1966. Very fresh.
Carrot cake really is not bad. And katong laksa also not bad.
Prawn mee from the Penang stall not too bad for $3.50.

Stopover this perceived warm & claustrophobic place for late lunch seeing so many vacated carpark lots, and chose the seat facing Bukit Timah Hill and open space for a pleasant short chill-out moment.
Soy sauce chicken. My serving from Bukit Timah Eating House #01-197 came without chicken skin, the part I enjoy most when eating this style. The meat was overcooked — soft & almost falling off bone
Delicious fried oyster.. Great wok taste. Fresh oysters.
Try the chicken rice there 02-177! Addictive.
Try Ah Poh BBQ Seafood StingRay Yummy!!!
Cheap and tasty
The pasta (vongole) I tried here is really good and it's cheap! Beats pastamania :) pizzas r good too! Try them!!!
The satay here must try.. Worth the money
The carrot cake there is the best 👍

Glad I chose the satisfying semi-soupy Sliced Fish Bee Hoon with LaLa, topped with fragrant-bitter fried garlic and pork lard (to enhance flavour) from Prosperity Seafood White Bee Hoon stall #02-180.
New. #02-199, Mi Casa. Tapas. Yummy.
Love the cereal prawn! And met a kind person who gave me his unused 50cents coupon! :)
Bak Chor mee is good. Queues are long for braised duck etc.
ngeteh hijau,, pagi2 menenangkan pikiran sebelum kerja
Old school carrot/radish cake
A lift now operates between both levels, helping the disabled get to their favorite carrot cake.
Try the BBQ chicken wings and the famous satay beehoon.
Thunder tea rice
Try Mien First Pasta.. Yummy and cheap.
It has a new two lvl lift.
Carrot cake, satay bee hoon, Thai cuisine and many more
Try the 虾面 at the corner (: my favourite store!!
134 black carrot cake
try the fish soup, Awesome!
One of the most affordable food centers in Singapore
Carrot cake is nice here.
$3. Can't find any flaw from stall 165.
Teo chew Fishball mee pok dry is nice - complete with old school orange fish cake! Stall is near to main staircase.
Avoid fruit juice stall in the middle next to Mutton Soup/opposite Poh Piah stall. Plump botak man collects $ & then uses same hand to handle fruits. No sense of food hygiene.
Try the oyster omelette! Pop the BBQ chicken wings stall. One of the best ard!
A cockroach climbed up my plate when i was eating! After that i saw another one on the opposite table.... Yucks! Food is wonderful, but cleanliness is zero.
Must eat the 五香
Don't miss the Kway Tiao Soup in the morning (while stock last) :)
Happy wonton mee!
The Grilled Stingray is AWESOME.
The laksa and the chicken udon <3
ah Poh BBQ seafood must try and please support!!! it's my relative stall!!
THE SATAY IS AWESOME ^^
Must try this
Try chicken rice 02-177 and Fish porridge 02-146.
He Zhong Carrot Cake! Die die must try!
Must try de pasta near e soya bean,soya bean drink opp of e buildings,hokien mee,porridge&handmade; noodle,MANY MANY TINS!! :)))
No worth for the fried prawn mee w signboard black in colour
Try the japanese and chicken rice stall. Imba (Y)
Nice food center, located on the 2nd floor, has many well known shop. The most famous is maybe Satay Bee Hoon. Hard to find seat in lunch time.
Dried food products provision shop in centre lane on ground floor is so much expensive than Hock Huat. Buy there only if you are desperate. 😱😱😱😱😱
Get the carrot cake and satay bee hoon. Can skip the satay stall though.
Hong Kong Yummy Soups very soothing. Yong Seng satay a bit dry...rice a bit hard.
Peter Pan grilled chicken chop is the best @$5 with generous portion of meat and wedgers. Hard to find nowadays!
Char kuay teow fried by auntie opposite vegetable rice stall is so plain and oily. Not worth eating at $3.
Its my first time stopover this perceived warm & claustrophobic place for late lunch, as I'm too hungry before continuing work nearby. Will be back during non-peak meal hrs, so many good food here.
Zhong zhong fine spice wuxiang beehoon is good! Rem to ask for the sweet sauce!
Gotta eat the chwee kwey @ bukit timah! ((=
Yummy clear Tom Yam soup!
The satay bee Hoon Is nice! The spices in the gravy is unique and different fr whr I ate fr other hawkers. However the kangkong cuttlefish is a great disappointment!
Ah Poh BBQ Seafood must try! 
Nice I wish the food court consider this Raman.
#02-193 Char Kway Teow GOOD!!!
pizzaria creations' bolognaise pasta, happy wanton mee, meatball soup, carrot cake (only frm "lao ji hao" & if the old man is cooking. the rest aren't great). enjoy! :)
Try the teochew fishball noodles!!
Stingray from Ah Poh BBQ Seafood is awesome
New store that sells all things abalone
Try the fried oyster near the bbq chicken wing. $4 for 8-10 oysters. Not bad.
Try the fish soup - both batang and red snapper fish are nice but the red snapper is more expensive. Have your table number ready when you order
Peter Pans grilled fish is gross. Don't ever eat the fish there. Order chicken. Nice they serve with wedges and cold coleslaw. The pizzeria has the nicest seafood aglio olio with chili and clams!
Fishball noodles near the main stairs only so-so. Sea salt caramel & Swiss Chocolate ice cream from Ice Cream Frenzy not worth the calories.
Best Chicken rice! Always long queue!!!
Chin Hock mutton soup has got the kick!
168 Congee tastes like home-cooked. No MSG
Hong kong yummy soups. Sell very nice brewed soup and it's cheap as well..
My go-to stall here is #02-145 Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee. Tasty food and generous servings. Thumbs up!
Horrible tasting carrot cake @He Zhong Carrot Cake (02-185). Dun ever try! Yucks!!!
tip top beef brisket stall is excellent. a rarity.
stall no #02-124 selling coffee drinks! boss farking yyppy! forget peolle's order still talk like one kind
Carrot cake
Xie Kee Hokkien Mee is a hidden gem (Y)
Try the bak chor mee and pig trotters noodles at Zhong Pin Noodle House #02-147
Why is smoking allowed in this public space? There are children and family using this food centre regularly.
Wanton mee: Too much MSG in WTM fr He Xin #02-128 :-( What started as a yummy 5-min meal ended up with tongue numbness for over an hour
It's actually called bukit timah food centre.
Try 133 Penang authentic fried kway teow!!! Nice!!! But for dinner, they only start fried kway teow after 630pm. Other food like prawn noodle soup is available all time!!!!
Carrot cake here is still the best! Love it!
Ah Poh bbq seafood: stingray, craypot bean curd prawn
Dec 2016: Bring mum here for tea break ~ popular He Zhong Carrot Cake (from #02-185). She's already eyeing on Satay & Hokkien Mee here for me to da-bao home next time when I'm here before meal hour 😅
The new yong tao Fu stall is decent. Samosas are crispy and savory but the sausages are a wee bit too blend.
Hup Cheong drink stall has very good coffee.
Here sells the famous nice tapioca! You should try it!
Kuey chap closed on Wednesday.
OMG! They still use traditional ketupat that even Malay don't use any more! Leng Kee #02-144 open till 11pm
25 minute wait carrot cake!!! Worth it!!!
Fish porridge is the best!
Carrot Cake & Chicken Chop Spaghetti MUST TRY!
Chin hock mutton soup is my favourite!
Chicken rice! Come by before 3pm if not it'd most likely be sold out.
The Penang char quay teow is good! But do not order the big plate!
138 Kway Chap is one of the best around!
Try the raw fish from the hong kong porridge stall!
Satay bee hoon is nice.. Then the kokkien prawn noodle just beside the main stair, is a die hard must try..
Mi Casa #02-199: Squid in lemon and olive oil ($6.2)
the satay n bbq chicken wings r good
Makanan enak, tersedia Halal Food juga
The hokkien prawn mee here is the BEST! ^^
try yam paste 02-176, fish porridge 02-146.
Love the mutton soup (not the beauty world one), satay bee hoon, tasty Thai Hut, hokkien mee, and now there is ice cream too!
Happy Wanton Noodle is really good ah! Don try can go die
Tasty Thai hut is amazing! <3
Carrot cake, fried black mee and 蚝fried is nice too! My favourite!
He Zhong Carrot Cake just $2 nice and cheap
Chicken rice: Seng Heng #02-177 serves a delicious plate but I wouldn't wait 20-30mins (unless it's craving day)
satay beehoon is a must try!! the hokkien mee beside the bak kut teh stall also superb!
Love the Satay Bee Hoon here! It's a must try!
no muslim food here.
Pasta from Mien (forgot to take note of the stall no! The signboard is in red) is good & cheap ($4 on average with reasonable portions)! Here's my chicken & mushroom pasta in cream sauce! 
Carrot cake, satays and chicken wings here a must try!
Penang char kway teow quite decent for $4
Morning favourites are the kway chap and Sheng Cheng noodles.
Try leng kee fish soup! Lots of fish and soup is super nice :) Happy wanton noodle gives lots of char siew and veg but I find the taste so so.
2 of my fav stalls - 133 Penang CKT ($4) and He Zhong Carrot Cake ($2). Waiting time was about 20 minutes each at 7pm on a Sunday. Best to come with more friends to help chop seats and queue!
Got one stall sells all kinds of beer like hoggarden and corona at cheap price
Xia Kee Hokkien Mee is nice
Try the fish ball noodles and laksa. The fish balls are hand-made.
Omg try the pasta shop. The one that sells thin crusted pizza.. Best pastas in the world!
The wanton mee stall has wind up already. Satay bee hoon standard also drop till....
Cheap and Good food
Porridge/congee. There are several stalls here but neighbours zoom in on 粥品 #01-121. Flavourful base of rice porridge. Comes with a free stick of yutiao (fried dough fritters)
138 Kway chap!
The handicap uncle that sings here on saturday morning is - not to be missed!
Leng Kee Satay, fried oyster n chicken wings :D must try !!
Clothes alteration services: There r @ least 4 shops on d 1st flr offering to shorten ur pants length, adjust waist size, etc. D most active appears 2 b unit 77
if you are looking at soya beancurd tasting like old airport road, kampong boy is a disappointment...
Stall 133, Not Worth Trying! Bad attitude and very small portion for the $4 price.
The auntie at Xin Heng Fried Kway Teow has a face machiam I owe her a living... Blacklisted! Regardless of whether her food is gd or not
The fish & chips at PETER PANS,is very delicious!!
